This paper deals with the problem of behavior planning for autonomous vehicles, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a framework that incorporates machine learning techniques such as QMDP and Monte Carlo tree search, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of sensor data and uncertainty, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV).
